AB  - The paper establishes (necessary and sufficient) conditions for the local identifiability of multivariate linear time series models with measurement errors. The models have a linear relation with rational transfer (matrix) function and variables specified by unrestricted vector ARMA processes of fixed orders (or more general variables). The identifiability conditions (finally) are simple counting rules combining the order parameters of a model. The paper derives the results bydisplaying in detail a new identification method which is based on the factorization and the expansion into partial fractions of rational matrices.
