AB  - For describing the distribution of income, a family of maximum entropy density functions is derived under optional side conditions on the distance of the mean income from the minimum income and the absolute Gini index of concentration. Many of the resulting Lorenz curves, obtained from the reciprocal of the density function by repeated quadrature, turn out to be well-known models.
